            <h3 class=""medium_heading""> II. PEDAGOGICAL OBJECTIVES    </h3>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 1. Origin of the program   </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    With the growth of service and companies globaly, a skilled and marketing-trained workforce is required in the labour market. The two-year
                    Master in Marketing & International Management (MIM) meets this need.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 2. Objectives of the program</h3>
                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.1. General Objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The Master’s Degree in Marke");
            WriteLiteral(@"ting and International Management aims to train managers who are directly operational in companies in order to
                    help them with their internationalisation project. It is aimed at students who already have a general training in management and who have a good
                    level of English. The emphasis is on the marketing and strategic dimensions, without neglecting the other aspects of an internationalisation
                    approach.
                </p>

                <h3 class=""smaller_heading""> II.2.2. Specific Objectives </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    <strong> Commmun run to the mention </strong><br/>
                    Students holding this Master’s degree will therefore be able to act as managers (in-house) or as consultants (external). Their missions will be to :
                </p>
                <ul class=""one_list"">
                    <li> 
                        Develop strategies and implement a marketing plan
  ");
            WriteLiteral(@"                  </li>
                    <li> 
                        Create a distribution network
                    </li>
                    <li> 
                        Support companies in their internationalisation projects
                    </li>
                    <li> 
                        Supervise international project
                    </li>
                    <li> 
                        Conduct a market research
                    </li>
                </ul>


                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II.3. Program Approach </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    The Master’s programme in Marketing & International Management prepares students for the Management of International Organisations and for
                    the Careers of private companies with a focus on entrepreneurship.
                </p>

            </div>

        </figure>

